cs.LG, cs.IT, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.SI 

This paper presents a generalized structured regression framework based on mutual information measures, which are widely used in Machine Learning and Computer Vision. The paper specifically focuses on Sharma-Mittal divergence, a relative entropy measure, and its application in the Twin Gaussian Processes (TGP) framework. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also includes experimental evaluations on several datasets, which suggests a potential fit for cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) sub-categories.
